Laura S. McCall, as Executrix, &c., Appellant, v. Arthur B. Proal, et al., Respondents. Decided May 3, 1886. Appeal from judgment entered on the dismissal of complaint on the pleadings. D. M. Porter, for appellant. Thomas F. Wentworth and Felix Jellenik, for respondents.

Before Freedman and Ingraham, JJ.

Opinion

Per Curiam.

Judgment reversed ; new trial ordered; costs to abide event.
